I’m glad I gave this place a try today! I was debating if I shall get devil dawgs for a late lunch, or try this place for the first time ever! And I went with: let’s try something new! So I went in and checked the menu out. And I ordered a chorizo burrito, and horchata drink.  I was scared at first to try the horchata cause I had a horchata before at some Taco Diner out in the suburbs because I didn’t like the way the suburbs made theirs. I tried it at Taco Diner, and it tasted so spicy/bitter that I gagged and spat it out. Yet Taco Maya’s horchata is so good! It felt like I was drinking a pumpkin spiced milkshake when I had it. So the taco diner down in the suburbs had to have really messed up badly. Cause some of my fellow Hispanic friends I have told me before that Horchata is supposed to be sweet with a hint of cinnamon, and taste like a milkshake. And If it tastes bitter, they messed up bad! So Taco Maya you did a good job with the horchata drink!!!! I was hesitant at first cause of the bad experience I had with the horchata in the suburbs in taco diner. Yet you guys made me love horchatas today!!!  It was only my second time today ever having a horchata in my life. I gave it a risk, and I loved it! So thank you so much for changing my view on horchatas. Cause your guys horchata is so good that I literally just finished drinking the whole cup of it just now!!!  Definitely will come back again soon. You earned to yourself a new customer. 😊❤️

Was actually on my way to another nearby familiar Mexican spot over on Printer's Row, when this place caught my attention. First because it was new---or at least new to me. Second, I noticed a few other people at tables inside (quite appropriately socially-distanced) and the energetic staff busily working behind the counter. Even though they were all wearing masks as mandated, the place seemed inviting. After finally settling on one Yucatan and one Shrimp taco, I finally placed my order, including sides of refried beans and rice. The employee assisting me suggested making it a plate/combo. This was appreciated as saving a little cash on a deal is always a good thing! Chips and salsa as an appetizer were included, and I had to remember to save room for the main dish! Everything arrived at my table hot and looked very appetizing. Although the tacos seemed small at first, they were stuffed with very tasty combinations of ingredients in just the right amounts. The shrimp were a tad salty, but otherwise, no complaints. This was a great choice for a quick flavorful meal in a bright, clean, and casual spot.

On the other hand, they have delicious salsa's and the chips- though I didn't try them- looked fresh. In short, I really wanted to like it but it was meh and sadly, with all the Mexican joints in town, I don't have reason to go back.  P.S. I find it interesting that the owners reply to the 5 star reviews only. Those are the "awesome customers". Well I'm an awesome customer too. I just wish I had an awesome experience. Had like an 11 Used Ritual to order at 8:35pm for pickup at 8:51pm. The dude said, “yeah, Ritual is just a third party so...” At 9pm, they advised they were making the food. At 9:10, they were still making it, so I asked if they could just cancel it because I was almost ready for bed ... They advised that I would have to call Ritual. And so I said, “I’ve already paid upfront so I’ll still take it.” I went back outside and came back in a few minutes later... Somewhere along my night of going back and forth from their pick-up counter, they misconstrued what I said and realized that I still wanted the order. But at 9:23pm, one of their team came outside with my order to deliver to me as I was waiting with my dog.  Unfortunately, I give their Ritual platform integration, operations (rollout), and service a big fat zero. They gave me half a box of chips instead of a full one; along with the wrong salsa. The add-on order container of guacamole was also not filled to full capacity. The chicken tamale was half steamed soft whilst the other half was a kind of a dryer, hardened feel - kind of like when you reheat food in the microwave instead of steaming it.  So, the positives that move up the average score: - Store team was nice and were quite busy - The Steak torta was delicious

Wow! This place was soooo good! Let's start out with the chips. They are free, which is nice but they are not like any other tortilla chips. They have this wonderful seasoning that makes them slightly salty and perfect. I ordered a 3 taco plate and elotes. While I loved the steak taco (seasoned well and so tender) and the Dorado (fish was crispy on outside, fluffy in the middle) , the Signature is where it's at! So many layer of flavors! It isn't on the big menu but it's on the menu on the counter  It has steak, bacon, pineapple, avocado, cheese, onions and chipotle mayo. It's sweet and salty and the textures are great. My friend got the fries a la Mexicana for us to share, which is Waffle fries with nacho toppings and it was also delicious. It had queso cheese, jajapenos, tomatoes, steak, refried beans, sour cream, and guacamole. I had never had Waffle fries with those toppings but it works! There was also a salsa bar so you can pair your food with the salsa of your choice  I am a wuss and got the mild, which was green and it was also delicious. I cannot wait to go back!

We ordered food tonight at 8pm. Around 8:45, we got an email saying our food would be delivered at 8:54. 15 minutes later we called and they said it would be delivered in 5 minutes. I called again 15 minutes later when our food still wasn't here and asked for a refund and to cancel the order. The manager promised to refund our order but said the food would still arrive. It is now 10:11 pm and still no tacos. I will never order from here again.

Meh! I wasn’t overly impressed or underwhelmed with this place.  It was ok. My biggest dissatisfaction was with the meat. I ordered a steak taco salad and a grilled chicken taco. The steak was excessively chewy, dry, and flavorless. Now in the salad with all the garnishments,  it wasn’t so bad, but the salad could’ve been next level had the meat been prepared better. The chicken was also very dry, over cooked, and flavorless. I could’ve done without. I don’t feel like you’re missing out on anything here, but I wouldn’t  go as far as saying don’t eat here. The reviews overall are pretty good, which is why I decided to try them. Hopefully this was just a bad day.

I drove here on a Tuesday after work and parked on the main street and just paid for metered parking. I'm vegetarian, so I opted for the Quesadilla dinner. It came with a side of rice and your choice of whole black beans or refried pinto beans. I've had both and they're both good. Food has good flavor. The quesadilla was delicious. It had the right amount of red and green bell peppers, but not so much that it feels like I'm having a fajita. The tortilla was cooked to golden perfection. I liked that they offer a variety of sauces, and you get to pour your own container of it. The service was great. Ambiance was just right. Not overpriced and I waited about 8-10 minutes for my food.
